    <p><strong>Planetary mixer prices in India in 2026 range from ₹18,000 for a basic 5-litre benchtop model to ₹4 lakh or more for a heavy-duty 60-litre floor-standing mixer.</strong> The planetary mixer is the most versatile commercial mixer — it handles cake batters, frostings, bread doughs, meringues, and everything in between. This guide helps you choose the right capacity and brand for your specific needs, with real prices from Indian suppliers.</p>

    <h2>What Is a Planetary Mixer?</h2>
    <p>A planetary mixer gets its name from how the attachment moves — it orbits the bowl (like a planet orbiting the sun) while also rotating on its own axis. This dual movement ensures thorough mixing of all ingredients, including those at the bottom and sides of the bowl.</p>
    <p>Every planetary mixer comes with three standard attachments:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Flat beater</strong> — for cake batters, cookie dough, mashed potatoes, and general mixing</li>
      <li><strong>Dough hook</strong> — for bread doughs, pizza dough, and other stiff doughs</li>
      <li><strong>Wire whisk</strong> — for whipping cream, egg whites, meringues, and light batters</li>
    </ul>

